title.narrative: SYSTEM STRENGTHENING FOR NEWBORN HEALTH

description.narrative: Strengthened institutional capacity for delivery of quality health services for newborns and their caregivers., which contributes to Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Maternal And Newborn Health, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Pmtct And Infant Male Circumcision, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Access to, and quality of health and related services and systems is strengthened by 2021

description.narrative: UNICEF engaged in advocacy efforts with local and Caribbean regional partners to call for the implementation of front of package warning labels on food products. ;As it regards, infant and young child feeding, the public health sector has remained resolute in promoting good practices in the face of the pandemic and with UNICEF’s support of the capacity of 266 health care staff was increased to provide support to parents of young children up to age 5.; Additionally, Jamaica Moves in Schools continued to be implemented among 200 schools through implementation of online activities promoting movement during and between classes. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:25/01/2022
